data.enText: a tree with smooth bark and thin branches, that grows in northern countries
the hard pale wood of the birch tree

data.chText: 用桦木条抽打（作为惩罚）
data.enText: the practice of hitting sb with a bunch of birch sticks, as a punishment

means: 用桦木条抽打(作为惩罚)

tr: a switch consisting of a twig or a bundle of twigs from a birch tree
used to hit people as punishment
example: my father never spared the birch

tr: any betulaceous tree or shrub of the genus Betula having a thin peeling bark
hard close-grained wood of any of various birch trees
used especially in furniture and interior finishes and plywood
consisting of or made of wood of the birch tree

value.def: A birch is a type of tall tree with thin branches.
The birch is a punishment in which someone is hit with a wooden stick.
